WEBVTT

00:02.203 --> 00:03.602
One grand a month.
I'm worth more than that.

00:03.671 --> 00:05.338
One of you is sending money
to Indonesia.

00:05.406 --> 00:07.139
Livengood's using it
as probable cause.

00:07.208 --> 00:09.808
You want to know before he drops
a warrant, right?

00:09.877 --> 00:11.276
Renn left and took Nick.

00:11.346 --> 00:14.013
She'll come back.
Yeah. I don't know.

00:14.081 --> 00:15.881
You didn't see the look
on her face.

00:15.950 --> 00:17.482
You sending money
to Adrian?

00:17.484 --> 00:19.952
The guy I use
is untraceable.
What guy?

00:20.021 --> 00:21.954
Guy over at the liquor store
on Ditmar.

00:22.023 --> 00:23.488
I give him cash.

00:23.490 --> 00:25.758
His connection in Jakarta
gives Adrian the money.

00:25.826 --> 00:27.092
There's no trace.

00:27.161 --> 00:29.562
I'm Billy, by the way.
Nice to meet you, Billy.

00:29.630 --> 00:31.697
Taking it for a run
down to Mexico next week.

00:31.766 --> 00:34.033
You should come.
I can't.

00:34.101 --> 00:36.035
I've had a few things
go sideways.

00:36.103 --> 00:37.436
I'm down a few contacts,

00:37.504 --> 00:39.772
and it's harder
to make things happen that way.

00:39.840 --> 00:42.174
J's the one who approached me
about the fence.

00:42.243 --> 00:44.543
So why are you here?

00:45.446 --> 00:48.181
Max: You're gonna kick me
30% of your take

00:48.249 --> 00:52.385
between Pendleton
and National City.

00:52.453 --> 00:53.318
Deal.

00:53.388 --> 00:54.519
[ Water splashing ]

00:54.589 --> 00:55.721
Get out.

00:55.723 --> 00:56.722
Please don't do this.

00:56.791 --> 00:58.391
[ Groans ]

00:59.194 --> 01:01.660
Hey!
You can't leave me out here!

01:01.729 --> 01:03.462
Parker Freeman
from Sun of a Beach.

01:03.530 --> 01:06.198
I think there may have been some
confusion with my liquor order.

01:06.267 --> 01:07.466
I just want my shit back.

01:07.534 --> 01:09.935
[ Grunts ]
[ Patrons murmuring ]

01:09.937 --> 01:11.604
Trying to pull some shit
on me?

01:11.672 --> 01:14.006
You were trying to
set me up!
Wait a minute.

01:14.075 --> 01:15.208
I don't know what
you're talking about.

01:15.276 --> 01:17.743
Who showed up?
DEA. Livengood.

01:17.745 --> 01:21.680
The only thing these guys
seemed to care about was Deran.

01:21.749 --> 01:26.419
♪♪

01:26.487 --> 01:32.225
♪ She stares deeply

01:32.293 --> 01:36.295
♪ Locked inside me

01:36.363 --> 01:38.998
♪ Burnin' brightly

01:41.636 --> 01:47.172
♪ One they know
that I cannot take ♪

01:47.241 --> 01:50.976
♪ Waitin' for it all to begin

01:51.045 --> 01:55.014
♪ Every night now, they'll win

01:58.119 --> 02:01.120
♪ Come and meet my black hole

02:01.188 --> 02:04.924
♪ Got a big black hole

02:04.992 --> 02:08.593
♪ Got a big black hole

02:08.595 --> 02:11.931
♪ I've got a big black hole

02:12.599 --> 02:16.802
♪ I've got a big black,
big black hole ♪

02:16.804 --> 02:20.139
♪ Got a big black hole
inside of me ♪

02:20.207 --> 02:22.708
♪ Got a

02:24.679 --> 02:26.211
How's the hand?

02:26.213 --> 02:29.582
Better than their faces.

02:34.355 --> 02:35.888
Got an idea for a job.

02:35.957 --> 02:37.290
Oh, yeah?
Yeah.

02:37.358 --> 02:39.158
You, uh, you know
what a hawala is?

02:39.226 --> 02:40.759
No.

02:40.828 --> 02:42.695
So, say you want to send money
to another country, right?

02:42.763 --> 02:46.231
No record.
You pay this guy, the hawala.

02:46.233 --> 02:48.501
He's got another guy
in the other country

02:48.569 --> 02:50.703
basically sitting on cash.

02:50.771 --> 02:53.172
He sends that guy a text
with a code word, and then --

02:53.240 --> 02:54.773
The person
you're sending the money to

02:54.842 --> 02:56.909
shows up with the code word
and collects the cash.

02:56.978 --> 03:01.180
Yeah. It's like an underground
Western Union.

03:01.248 --> 03:02.982
Okay.

03:03.050 --> 03:07.220
Jess, Adrian's sister, she was
using one to send him money.

03:09.724 --> 03:11.590
Is she still doing it?

03:11.659 --> 03:13.058
No.

03:13.060 --> 03:14.593
[ Cellphone buzzing ]

03:14.662 --> 03:19.565
So, what's the job?
We rip off this hawala?

03:20.267 --> 03:21.867
Uh, we'll talk about it
later.

03:21.936 --> 03:25.804
I got some bullshit
I got to deal with at the bar.

03:25.873 --> 03:27.940
Is there anything
I can check out?

03:28.009 --> 03:29.542
Uh, yeah.

03:29.610 --> 03:31.944
There's a guy that works
out of the Aero Mart on Ditmar.

03:32.013 --> 03:34.714
Maybe you can go over there
and check out the security.

03:35.816 --> 03:36.882
All right.

03:36.884 --> 03:40.686
All right.
I'll see you later.

03:40.688 --> 03:50.162
♪♪

03:50.231 --> 03:51.430
♪ Saw a girl in Tampa

03:51.498 --> 03:53.966
♪ I asked her for a date

03:54.035 --> 03:57.302
♪ She said,
"Baby, I'm a sailor ♪

03:57.372 --> 03:58.771
♪ This thing better wait"

03:58.839 --> 04:01.707
♪ I said, "I don't believe you

04:01.776 --> 04:04.043
♪ "Would you show me
some proof?" ♪

04:04.111 --> 04:08.047
[ Tires screech, engine revs ]

04:08.115 --> 04:09.915
♪ She showed me her tattoo

04:09.917 --> 04:11.050
Truck's on fire!

04:11.118 --> 04:12.985
♪ Then I knew
that that's the truth ♪

04:13.054 --> 04:15.721
Your truck is on fire!

04:18.059 --> 04:20.659
♪ Eye for an eye
♪ That's the truth

04:20.728 --> 04:22.728
♪ And a tooth for a tooth

04:24.131 --> 04:27.866
♪ Pulled out a .44
♪ That's the truth

04:27.935 --> 04:29.735
♪ Now I know
that that's the truth ♪

04:29.737 --> 04:31.203
♪ That's the truth

04:31.272 --> 04:34.006
♪ That's the truth
♪ That's the truth

04:34.075 --> 04:35.274
♪♪

04:35.342 --> 04:36.942
What the hell?

04:37.011 --> 04:38.143
Don't turn around.

04:38.212 --> 04:41.346
Aw, God damn it.
Yeah. You get it.

04:41.416 --> 04:43.148
Let's take a walk.

04:43.217 --> 04:45.284
[ Engine idling ]

04:45.352 --> 04:47.420
Nice and easy.

04:48.623 --> 04:50.890
All right.
Keep it up.

04:50.958 --> 04:53.426
Say hi to my friends.

04:53.494 --> 04:56.361
[ Laughs ]
Nice truck.

04:56.431 --> 04:59.164
What do you got, big guy?

04:59.166 --> 05:02.034
There it is.
Cute gun, Sally.

05:02.103 --> 05:04.770
Take his glasses off.
I can't see
without my glasses.

05:04.839 --> 05:06.505
No shit?

05:06.573 --> 05:08.507
Cross your legs
and make yourself comfortable.

05:08.575 --> 05:10.843
Whoo!
Bingo, baby.

05:10.912 --> 05:14.447
You goddamn druggie
freak sons of bitches.

05:14.515 --> 05:16.115
Here we go.

05:16.183 --> 05:18.517
Top-of-the-line VCR,
baby.

05:18.586 --> 05:20.119
Yeah.
♪ She can do it all night long

05:20.187 --> 05:23.055
♪ She's a bad girl

05:23.124 --> 05:25.991
♪ She's a bad girl

05:26.060 --> 05:31.730
♪♪

05:31.799 --> 05:33.266
[ Keys jingling ]

05:34.401 --> 05:36.401
Rendezvous
back at your place?

05:36.403 --> 05:37.602
Yeah. Sure.
Uh, I can't.

05:37.604 --> 05:38.737
I got to meet Cheryl.

05:38.806 --> 05:41.474
Uh, Cheryl kicked you out,
Jake.

05:41.542 --> 05:43.476
We're meeting up
to talk.

05:43.544 --> 05:45.478
Hey, it's fine.
Leave him alone.

05:45.546 --> 05:48.080
You can help me in the morning,
can't you, Manny?

05:48.149 --> 05:50.816
Yeah.
No problem.

05:50.818 --> 05:54.854
Hey, yo.
This place is freakin' dope.

05:55.890 --> 05:58.423
Hey, why doesn't your brother
live here?

05:58.425 --> 06:00.425
Broken heart.
[ Sniffs ]

06:00.495 --> 06:02.428
So why are you here?

06:09.103 --> 06:10.503
You heard from Renn?

06:11.638 --> 06:13.639
Not even a text.

06:16.911 --> 06:18.377
What'd you do?

06:18.445 --> 06:20.379
[ Sniffs ]
What'd<i> I</i> do?

06:20.447 --> 06:22.648
Yeah. You must have done
something, right?

06:22.717 --> 06:25.584
It'll suck if your kid
has to grow up with a stepdad.

06:25.653 --> 06:27.987
Ain't gonna be a stepdad,
man.

06:28.055 --> 06:29.388
Mine kicked me out

06:29.456 --> 06:31.390
after he caught me
going through his stash.

06:31.458 --> 06:33.859
Thanks for letting us
crash here, dude.

06:33.861 --> 06:37.997
Yeah. Well, you want to stay,
how about you just stop talking?

06:38.065 --> 06:39.932
All right?

06:45.606 --> 06:47.940
J:
What's up?

06:50.945 --> 06:53.546
I got to get rid
of this truck.

06:55.216 --> 06:58.951
It's got to be worth
at least 40 grand, right?

06:59.020 --> 07:00.753
I can't sell it.

07:00.821 --> 07:03.288
Some shit went down
in the desert.

07:03.290 --> 07:04.690
What about the engine?

07:04.692 --> 07:07.560
I don't want to take
any chances.

07:07.628 --> 07:10.363
Do you want me
to take care of this?

07:11.899 --> 07:13.298
No, I got it.

07:13.300 --> 07:15.468
All right.

07:18.639 --> 07:20.239
[ Horn honks, vehicles passing ]

07:20.307 --> 07:25.278
What's up, amigos?
I got VCRs, still in the box.

07:27.915 --> 07:29.314
How much?

07:29.316 --> 07:31.184
$400.

07:31.252 --> 07:33.719
Hey, that's half off
retail.

07:33.721 --> 07:37.590
Hey, you got any of that, um,
that X-rated stuff?

07:37.658 --> 07:39.058
[ Chuckles ]
Hell yeah.

07:39.126 --> 07:41.060
Buy a machine,
I'll throw in a tape.

07:42.196 --> 07:43.796
$375.

07:44.665 --> 07:47.800
[ Sighs ] Come on, man.
You're killin' me.

07:49.737 --> 07:51.904
All right. Come on.
$375.

07:54.475 --> 07:58.477
All right.
See my pretty girl over there?

07:58.545 --> 08:00.613
She'll take care of you.

08:05.953 --> 08:08.153
Here you go.

08:08.222 --> 08:10.022
"Jailhouse Moms"
for you.

08:11.092 --> 08:13.860
And for you...

08:14.829 --> 08:18.163
...let's go with
"Rhonda Goes to Vegas."

08:18.232 --> 08:19.298
Oh!

08:19.366 --> 08:21.033
That one has
a decent story.

08:21.102 --> 08:22.367
Thanks.
All right.

08:22.369 --> 08:24.537
Have fun, boys.

08:25.706 --> 08:28.373
Well, that's it
for this place.

08:28.375 --> 08:31.777
I don't know where else
in Irvine to hit up.

08:31.846 --> 08:33.579
No. It's fine.
We're done.

08:33.648 --> 08:36.315
I'm gonna keep this one
for the kids.

08:36.383 --> 08:37.650
That's a pricey gift.

08:37.718 --> 08:40.519
Yeah, but worth every penny
if it shuts them up.

08:40.588 --> 08:43.589
[ Chuckles ]

08:43.658 --> 08:46.258
Here you go.

08:46.327 --> 08:47.926
It's all there.

08:47.995 --> 08:49.128
I know it is.

08:49.196 --> 08:52.331
You gonna take Jake his cut,
give it to his wife?

08:52.399 --> 08:54.733
[ Chuckles ]
No. No need.

08:54.802 --> 08:56.135
He'll come sniffin' around

08:56.203 --> 08:58.471
as soon as Cheryl kicks him out
again.

08:59.406 --> 09:00.473
See you later.

09:00.541 --> 09:01.940
All right.

09:02.009 --> 09:03.943
[ Door closes, engine starts ]

09:12.419 --> 09:14.554
[ Engine shuts off ]

09:16.423 --> 09:18.991
[ Door opens, metal rattling ]

09:25.900 --> 09:28.901
Whoa.
What's going on?

09:28.970 --> 09:30.169
Liquor board?

09:30.237 --> 09:33.105
They just showed up and started
taking all the booze.

09:33.174 --> 09:35.240
Excuse me.
What's the deal here?

09:35.310 --> 09:36.642
You the owner?
Yeah.

09:36.711 --> 09:39.444
We got orders
to confiscate your inventory.

09:39.446 --> 09:41.314
And why is that?
It's all in there.

09:41.382 --> 09:43.782
What are you talking about?
This doesn't tell me shit.

09:43.851 --> 09:45.050
Hold on.
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

09:45.119 --> 09:46.519
You got to let me
read this first, man.

09:46.587 --> 09:48.187
Hey, you interfere,
you're getting arrested.

09:48.255 --> 09:50.389
That's bullshit! I'm up to date
on all my permits.

09:50.457 --> 09:52.191
Take it up with the board.

09:52.259 --> 09:54.860
It's those assholes from Sun
of a Beach down the street, huh?

09:54.929 --> 09:58.331
All the information on your
hearing date is in the summons.

09:58.399 --> 09:59.732
Shit.

09:59.800 --> 10:01.133
They can just shut you down
like this?

10:01.202 --> 10:03.068
Yeah. It's the liquor board.
They're low-rent.

10:03.070 --> 10:05.470
You give 'em $10, they'll
suck off their own fathers.

10:05.540 --> 10:07.139
Receipt for
your inventory.

10:07.208 --> 10:08.807
You're shut down
till the hearing.

10:08.876 --> 10:10.609
Have a nice day.

10:10.678 --> 10:13.880
[ Door closes ]

10:17.084 --> 10:26.958
♪♪

10:26.960 --> 10:36.502
♪♪

10:36.570 --> 10:39.805
[ Mid-tempo music playing
on radio ]

10:41.175 --> 10:43.643
Hi. I'd, uh,
like to send some money.

10:43.711 --> 10:46.445
No problem. We do Western Union
and money orders.

10:46.514 --> 10:48.514
Actually,
I'm looking for something

10:48.582 --> 10:51.551
a little more, uh,
informal.

10:54.322 --> 10:56.589
I think you have
the wrong address.

10:58.726 --> 11:01.727
Y-You've been helping out
my sister.

11:01.795 --> 11:03.195
Uh, she comes in here

11:03.197 --> 11:04.864
and sends money to our brother
in Indonesia.

11:04.932 --> 11:07.799
I just want to send him
some, too.

11:07.869 --> 11:09.935
Uh, my -- my sister's name
is -- is Jess,

11:10.004 --> 11:12.338
and our brother's name
is Adrian.

11:12.406 --> 11:13.673
We don't do names.

11:13.741 --> 11:16.008
I told your sister that,
and now I'm telling you.

11:16.077 --> 11:17.609
Oh, I'm sorry.
I'm sorry.

11:17.679 --> 11:21.080
Um, what's your rate?

11:21.148 --> 11:22.682
Five percent.

11:22.750 --> 11:24.149
For sending or receiving?

11:24.218 --> 11:25.418
Both.

11:26.087 --> 11:27.486
Great.

11:27.555 --> 11:31.691
Um, well, I'm selling my car,
so I'll have 20 grand next week.

11:31.759 --> 11:33.059
Too much.

11:34.495 --> 11:36.562
Uh, 10?

11:36.630 --> 11:39.498
$1,000 max.

11:40.301 --> 11:44.036
I'll pay you a higher rate,
make it worth your time.

11:44.038 --> 11:47.239
Look, I handle old ladies
in New Delhi

11:47.241 --> 11:50.442
getting grocery money
from their sons.

11:50.444 --> 11:54.046
Or people like your sister,
sending 500 bucks at a time.

11:55.783 --> 12:00.086
My friend...
we're in the Aero Mart.

12:01.322 --> 12:03.188
Yeah.

12:03.257 --> 12:05.457
Thanks.

12:05.459 --> 12:11.330
♪♪

12:11.399 --> 12:17.403
♪♪

12:17.471 --> 12:19.338
[ Knock on door ]

12:19.407 --> 12:21.574
Candace!
Open up!

12:23.745 --> 12:26.145
Look, I know she's in there!

12:27.214 --> 12:28.848
Candace!

12:30.684 --> 12:33.019
She's not here.
Oh, bullshit.

12:35.022 --> 12:36.488
Renn!

12:36.490 --> 12:38.290
I'm telling you.
Not here.

12:38.292 --> 12:40.226
Then where is she?
She called me,

12:40.294 --> 12:43.295
said she was going someplace
to get her thoughts together.

12:43.297 --> 12:44.563
Which is where?!

12:44.632 --> 12:46.365
Somewhere away
from you.

12:46.434 --> 12:48.167
Renn!

12:48.236 --> 12:49.835
Look, he's my son,

12:49.904 --> 12:51.837
and I have a right
to know where he is.

12:51.906 --> 12:54.573
You got to look around.
Now leave.

12:54.642 --> 12:56.375
Tell me where he is.

12:56.444 --> 12:59.178
You're high right now.

12:59.247 --> 13:01.313
This is why I wanted the baby
with me.

13:01.315 --> 13:03.916
Oh, so that's what
this is about, isn't it?

13:03.985 --> 13:06.185
This is about my daughter
coming to her senses

13:06.253 --> 13:09.188
and getting away from you.

13:09.257 --> 13:16.328
♪♪

13:16.397 --> 13:18.731
[ Engine starts ]

13:28.209 --> 13:29.609
[ Engine shuts off ]

13:31.945 --> 13:34.146
Pope.
What's up, Ralphie?

13:34.215 --> 13:36.616
I need to lose
this truck.

13:36.684 --> 13:39.719
Sorry, man.
Can't help this time.

13:43.691 --> 13:45.891
What's up?

13:45.959 --> 13:47.359
Can't do business
with you.

13:47.361 --> 13:50.696
To be honest, can't even talk
to you or your brothers.

13:50.764 --> 13:52.932
Why is that?

13:54.302 --> 13:55.868
No. Tell me.
Why?

13:57.771 --> 13:59.172
You got heat
on you, dude.

14:00.441 --> 14:01.973
Bullshit.

14:01.975 --> 14:04.376
Came from Pete.
The DEA.

14:04.445 --> 14:07.313
He says we're supposed to stay
away from the Codys for a while.

14:12.986 --> 14:15.054
Take the truck, Ralphie.

14:16.658 --> 14:18.590
Get off my lot.

14:18.660 --> 14:27.466
♪♪

14:27.535 --> 14:29.735
[ Engine revs ]

14:31.939 --> 14:34.674
[ Tires screech ]

14:34.742 --> 14:37.276
[ Engine revs ]

14:39.881 --> 14:42.948
[ Indistinct talking on radio ]

14:43.017 --> 14:45.718
[ Engines idling ]

14:49.891 --> 14:52.758
[ Engine revs, siren wails ]

14:54.228 --> 15:02.301
♪♪

15:02.370 --> 15:10.376
♪♪

15:10.444 --> 15:11.977
♪ And so it went

15:12.046 --> 15:15.715
♪ The children lost
their minds ♪

15:15.783 --> 15:17.649
♪ Beggin' for forgiveness

15:17.651 --> 15:19.985
♪ Was such a waste of time

15:20.054 --> 15:22.788
♪ And the bullets start to fly

15:22.856 --> 15:25.591
♪ And the bough's
about to break ♪

15:25.659 --> 15:27.927
♪ When you hear them cry

15:27.995 --> 15:29.995
♪ It's too much for me to take

15:30.064 --> 15:35.667
♪ They said the world
does not belong to you ♪

15:35.669 --> 15:38.404
♪ You are not the king

15:38.472 --> 15:40.540
♪ I am not the fool

15:40.608 --> 15:45.877
♪ They said the world
does not belong to you ♪

15:45.947 --> 15:49.014
♪ It don't belong to you

15:49.083 --> 15:52.952
♪ It belongs to me

15:53.020 --> 15:55.955
[ Engines revving,
siren wailing ]

15:57.959 --> 16:00.426
[ Tires screech ]

16:01.228 --> 16:07.032
♪ They said the world
does not belong to you ♪

16:07.101 --> 16:09.835
♪ It belongs to me

16:09.904 --> 16:20.046
♪♪

16:25.052 --> 16:27.787
Hey, Max.
Got your cut.

16:27.855 --> 16:30.389
[ Birds crying ]

16:31.125 --> 16:32.592
I boosted a bunch of tools
from a Sears,

16:32.660 --> 16:36.562
and I stuck up the night manager
of a video arcade.

16:37.398 --> 16:39.931
What about
those video machines

16:39.933 --> 16:42.134
that you were slinging
out of your car?

16:42.136 --> 16:45.137
That was in Irvine.

16:45.206 --> 16:47.306
What?
That's outside of your turf.

16:49.343 --> 16:50.776
My what?

16:52.280 --> 16:56.882
You said to me Pendleton
to National City.

16:56.951 --> 16:59.351
Irvine's outside of that.

16:59.420 --> 17:03.288
And what do I look like to you,
a goddamn Thomas Guide?

17:03.357 --> 17:06.692
You live in Oceanside.
You pay me tax.

17:06.760 --> 17:12.431
♪♪

17:12.500 --> 17:17.970
♪♪

17:18.039 --> 17:21.307
Get me rest of it.

17:21.375 --> 17:27.112
♪♪

